        "title": "Bus Topology",
        "content": "In a bus topology, all devices connect to a central cable, also known as the 'bus' or 'backbone'.\n\n*   **Simple Setup**: Easy to install and doesn't cost much.\n*   **Single Point of Failure**: If the main cable breaks, the whole network goes down.\n*   **Limited Scalability**: Adding more devices can slow down the network."
      },
