        "title": "Star Topology",
        "content": "In a star topology, each device connects to a central hub or switch.\n\n*   **Centralized Control**: Easier to manage and troubleshoot from one location.\n*   **Fault Tolerance**: If one device fails, it doesn't affect the rest of the network.\n*   **Cost**: Requires more cabling and a central hub, which can be more expensive than a bus topology."
      },
      {
        "title": "Ring Topology",
        "content": "In a ring topology, each device connects to exactly two other devices, forming a ring for data transmission.\n\n*   **Data Flow**: Data travels in one direction around the ring.\n*   **Failure Impact**: A break in the ring can disrupt the entire network.\n*   **Implementation**: Less commonly used today due to its limitations compared to star or mesh topologies."
